Products.RichDescription:
The Beechworth Honey Story

The Robinson family of Beechworth have been producing honey since the late 1880's. Benjamin Robinson became an apiarist after failing to find gold. Jodie & her husband Steven are part of the fourth generation of apiarists helping to produce pure and natural Beechworth honey.

Enjoy the best fruit all year around.

Angas Park Prunes are deliciously sweet, juicy and make a nutritious snack that is a source of dietary fibre. Proudly 100% Australian grown. they are picked at their peak then meticulously dried - hallmarks of the finest dried fruit. Bite into one and rest assured you've discovered the very best.

Angas Park Prunes are low in fat and cholesterol free. They are delicious eaten straight out of the pack or served in yoghurt or breakfast cereals.
